title: For Sale/Trade:   Lower Price! S&W 38-44 Outdoorsman Prewar Revolver
postcontent: Going to auction next week, lower price!Nice collector S&W 38-44 Outdoorsman Prewar revolver. This rare pistol was manufactured in 1932 and was built to handle the first 38 special +P. This came about because the police were out-gunned by the bad guys who were driving heavy duty cars with thick metal doors. Their 38 special service revolvers would not penetrate the doors. So, in 1931, S&W converted the 44 caliber N frame into the high powered 38 special +P. They called it the S&W Heavy Duty 38-44. This round was so popular with the police that the civilian population also wanted the high powered, low recoil pistol for hunting. Thus, S&W came out with the S&W 38-44 Outdoorsman with a 6 1/2" barrel. There was only 4,761 of these pistols built before WW2 broke out. The pistols built after the war had a "S" prefix before the serial number. This pistol has serial number 403XX. The right side pistol grip has matching serial number as well as the barrel. (They only stamped the right grip with serial number.) I would say this pistol is 85-90% condition. The grips are sharp, the barrel has holster wear near the muzzle on the left side,the right side of the barrel has four spots of blueing loss from the holster. There is also some freckling on the side plate. There is light blueing loss on the front edges of the cylinder as well as a turn ring. The bore looks shinny. I also have a leather period holster for it. Patended Dec. 25, 1928. Everything is tight on this pistol; end play, timing, lockup. I have shot a few standard 38 specials and can hit a beer can four out of six shots at 25 yds. These pistols have sold at auction for around thirty-five hundred to four thousand for a 95% pistol with the box. I have contacted a couple of auction houses and have got estimate sale prices at around the twenty-eight hundred mark. I'm offering up this gem for two thousand to you local collectors for a few weeks before it goes to auction. I would consider a very nice S&W model 66 old school, pinned and recessed with a three or four inch barrel as partial trade. Possibly a 686 also. IF you have a pistol, send pictures with your offer. I live in Wenatchee area and could do a halfway meet. Don't be afraid to make an offer!
